An ancient stone monolith that has stood for more than four millennia has had an enormous smiley face painted on it by vandals.

Historians were furious at discovering the protected Neolithic stone at the Brecon Beacons National Park in South Wales had been defaced with spray paint cans.

The Maen Llia standing stone was erected in the late Neolithic or early Bronze Age between 2,500 and 1,800 BC, experts believe.

