The iconic 12ft tall standing stone has stood in the Welsh hills since then undamaged - until vandals daubed an enormous smiling face across it.

The recognised site of national archaeological importance attracts visitors from around the world - and it is believed to be roughly as old as Stonehenge.

Devin and Marge Lemming, of Chicago, Illinois, said: ‘We were driving past and had to take a look.’

