Devin and Marge Lemming, of Chicago

The married couple added: ‘It’s staggering it has survived so long. This country has such great history - but why does someone try to spoil it? It’s a real shame someone had to try and ruin it.’

Brecon Beacons National Park Authority is working with Cadw, the Welsh Government’s historic environment service, and landowners to arrange for the graffiti to be ‘sensitively removed.’

Officials said the graffiti removal will be a slow and careful process undertaken by professionals.

